cluster_relations.rel_desc: Caterpillars take part in the biological process of pollination.
Butterflies play a crucial role in the process of pollination.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Subject organism functions as a pollinator contributing to the pollination process of the object.
args.justification: Both relations describe organisms (caterpillars, butterflies) playing a functional role in the biological process of pollination. A unified predicate 'acts_as_pollinator_in' captures that the subject serves as a pollinator within the pollination process, independent of wording differences like 'participates_in' or 'contributes_to'.

These relations express that the subject species fulfills an ecological/functional role (pollinator) in a biological process (pollination). Grouping them under 'ecosystem_function_role_relation' distinguishes them from generic participation or mere association relations.
The semantics emphasize the subject as an active agent performing an ecological function in a process, which aligns best with an AGENCY-type high-level group rather than simple ASSOCIATION.
